{"id":43342,"title":"15N2 label preparation (dissolved method)","title_html":"<p>15N2 label preparation (dissolved method)<\/p>","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png"},"doi":null,"doi_status":0,"uri":"15n2-label-preparation-dissolved-method-bnjnmcme","type_id":1,"template_id":1,"published_on":1617792229,"parent_protocols":[],"parent_collections":[],"cited_protocols":[],"version_id":0,"version_data":{"id":"0","code":"bnjnmcme","parent_id":0,"parent_uri":null,"is_same_owner":false,"has_pending_merge_request":false,"has_approved_merge_request":false},"created_on":1603074406,"modified_on":null,"categories":null,"public":1,"is_unlisted":0,"creator":{"name":"Molly A. Moynihan","affiliation":"Nanyang Technological University","affiliations":[],"username":"molly-moynihan","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/ad7352ff8927cf7908b7e16c6d04a306e9464b9764850ba3f375cde0f57eef4c\/crybhqee.jpg","placeholder":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/ad7352ff8927cf7908b7e16c6d04a306e9464b9764850ba3f375cde0f57eef4c\/crybhqee.jpg"},"badges":[{"id":3,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/silver.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/silver.svg"},"name":"Power author!"}],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"journal":null,"journal_name":null,"journal_link":null,"article_citation":null,"has_versions":0,"link":null,"total_collections":0,"number_of_steps":12,"authors":[{"name":"Molly Moynihan","affiliation":"Nanyang Technological University","affiliations":[],"username":"molly-moynihan","note":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/ad7352ff8927cf7908b7e16c6d04a306e9464b9764850ba3f375cde0f57eef4c\/crybhqee.jpg","placeholder":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/public\/ad7352ff8927cf7908b7e16c6d04a306e9464b9764850ba3f375cde0f57eef4c\/crybhqee.jpg"},"badges":[],"verified":1,"is_verified_user":true,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false}],"versions":[],"groups":[],"is_owner":1,"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":0,"is_bookmarked":0,"can_claim_authorship":0,"can_accept_authorship":0,"can_be_copied":1,"can_remove_fork":1,"fork_id":null,"url":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/view\/15n2-label-preparation-dissolved-method-bnjnmcme","forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"access":{"can_view":1,"can_remove":1,"can_add":0,"can_edit":0,"can_publish":0,"can_get_doi":1,"can_share":1,"can_move":1,"can_move_outside":1,"can_transfer":1,"can_download":1,"is_locked":0},"guid":"86C6F9D011B211EB9084D97187CE9039","state_version_id":1200,"steps":[{"id":1054035,"guid":"18FDB37011B311EB9084D97187CE9039","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F4EEC53D1C074DF88EB25507C986F5B0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Calculations"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"8DA774DB30B14A938DBEB9DB9F25AABF","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The following protocol is based on the dissolved gas method described by Mohr et al. 2010 and Klawoon et al. 2015. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>This protocol makes 4x 500mL serum bottles of <\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">15<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;vertical-align:super;vertical-align:sub;\">N<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span> labels enriched to ~90%. Enrichment of each serum bottle depends on the vacuum pressure used for degassing. The following calculations can be used to estimate degassing potential based on the vacuum pressure. <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>[N2]<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">seawater<\/span><span> = 0.000398 mol\/L = 398 mol\/L at 24\u00b0C, 1 atm<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>[N<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>] = TGP * X<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">N2<\/span><span>* k<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">H <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>[N<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span>] is the concentration of N<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span> after reaching equilibrium at pressure <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">p. <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\"> <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>TGP is the total gas pressure, which is the difference between atmospheric pressure (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;vertical-align:sub;\">p<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">atm<\/span><span>) and vacuum pressure (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;vertical-align:sub;\">p<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;vertical-align:sub;\">v<\/span><span>). (TGP = <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;vertical-align:sub;\">p<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">atm<\/span><span> - <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;vertical-align:sub;\">p<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;vertical-align:sub;\">v<\/span><span>).  <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">X<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">N2 <\/span><span>is the mole fraction of dinitrogen gas. X<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">N2 = <\/span><span>0.7804<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">k<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">H <\/span><span>is Henry's Law constant for nitrogen gas at 35ppt and 24\u00b0C. k<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">H = 0.00051 mol\/L atm<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\"><\/span><\/div><table border><tr style = \"text-align:center;\"><td>  <\/td><td>A<\/td><td>B<\/td><td>C<\/td><td>D<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">1<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">pv (mbar)<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">pv (atm)<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">[N2] mol\/L<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">Degassing %<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">2<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">200<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">0.20<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">0.000319444<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">20<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">3<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">600<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">0.59<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">0.000162324<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">59<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">4<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">950<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">0.94<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">0.000024845<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">94<\/td><\/tr><\/table><div class = \"text-block\">References: <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Klawonn, I., Lavik, G., B\u00f6ning, P.,  Marchant, H., Dekaezemacker, J., Mohr, W., & Ploug, H. (2015).  Simple approach for the preparation of 15\u2212 15N2-enriched water for  nitrogen fixation assessments: evaluation, application and  recommendations. <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Frontiers in microbiology<\/span><span>, <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">6<\/span><span>, 769.<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Mohr, W., Grosskopf, T., Wallace, D.  W., & LaRoche, J. (2010). Methodological underestimation of oceanic  nitrogen fixation rates. <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">PloS one<\/span><span>, <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">5<\/span><span>(9), e12583.<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"37D71390AAC642758737D33A12DBF147","order_id":2,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<table border><tr style = \"text-align:center;\"><td>  <\/td><td>A<\/td><td>B<\/td><td>C<\/td><td>D<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">1<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">pv (mbar)<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">pv (atm)<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">[N2] mol\/L<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">Degassing %<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">2<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">200<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">0.20<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">0.000319444<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">20<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">3<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">600<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">0.59<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">0.000162324<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">59<\/td><\/tr><tr><td style = \"text-align:center;\">4<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">950<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">0.94<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">0.000024845<\/td><td rowspan = \"\" colspan = \"\" style =\"display : table-cell;\">94<\/td><\/tr><\/table>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1054037,"guid":"442F85D011B511EB9084D97187CE9039","previous_id":1054035,"previous_guid":"18FDB37011B311EB9084D97187CE9039","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"163CAF605BF94AB4B922ADCE88C206EC","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"AA5EFB5651AA45CC802ECD27323A25C2","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Wash all glassware, tubing, rubber septa, etc. with 10% HCl and then rise 4x with Elga water (18.2M\u03a9). <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1054038,"guid":"9C3A47B011B511EB9084D97187CE9039","previous_id":1054037,"previous_guid":"442F85D011B511EB9084D97187CE9039","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F457AFF52531410E801B5250DFA6C896","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Preparation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9ADE402A91C449A38F066E4F6897CA6C","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Filter sterilize 3L of seawater using 0.22um pore size filters. Only ~2.5L of this is needed to fill serum bottles but it is good to have some extra when siphoning (step 5).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1054075,"guid":"448E675011B811EB9084D97187CE9039","previous_id":1054087,"previous_guid":"187DF7F011BA11EBB6288FB414C2DAB2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"2132A04E7F19413DA2F6A8D21F9C39AB","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Make label"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"3909C5D089B44EF0B4E693FCA180F52B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Shake serum bottles for a few minutes and then store horizontally, such that the gas bubble is not in contact with the septa. Store for 24 hours prior to use to increase dissolution (see Klawonn 2015 et al. Front. Microbiology)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Note: Injecting 100mL of this water into 1L incubation chambers gives an enrichment of ~9.7 atom% 15N2<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1054076,"guid":"FC6AFF1011B711EB9084D97187CE9039","previous_id":1054077,"previous_guid":"F858F94011B711EB9084D97187CE9039","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"AC0E5A1E3BE14C669AE891ADDDCBEC01","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Make label"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F414424D8F254447A8536BEAB26491C6","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Turn the serum bottle upside-down. Insert both the input and output needles\/syringes into the septa. Slowly inject the gas label. Injecting upside prevents any gas from escaping through the outflow. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1054077,"guid":"F858F94011B711EB9084D97187CE9039","previous_id":1054078,"previous_guid":"C1D7D68011B611EB9084D97187CE9039","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"84866E937988485F97D4F11E5DEF16D9","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Make label"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"D6BF3EA5AF3241408D9E275D39C70F5E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>When preparing gas syringe, flush any tubing\/syringe being used 2x with <\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">15<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;vertical-align:sub;\">N<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span> gas to remove any air. <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1054078,"guid":"C1D7D68011B611EB9084D97187CE9039","previous_id":1054079,"previous_guid":"7A91D5F011B611EB9084D97187CE9039","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"D1122098941E4E7AA263562BB38E224C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Make label"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"8187CE7DB2514D63B851A9EE5E62ADA5","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Using a needle and syringe, inject <\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">15<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;vertical-align:sub;\">N<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span> gas in a ratio of 2ml\/100mL into serum bottles (i.e. 11 mL for a 500mL serum bottle, as the headspace free volume is 550mL). A second needle and syringe should be used during injection as an outflow. <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1054079,"guid":"7A91D5F011B611EB9084D97187CE9039","previous_id":1054080,"previous_guid":"DB4D6F9011B511EB9084D97187CE9039","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7F8B42E3C7544E82A578ACFBE8641838","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Make label"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"0A9C5440046B42EE84F7D954611A2F1E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Using the siphon, fill serum bottles headspace free and crimp seal. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Depending on the rubber septa used, this step can be tricky and requires a bit of practice to not introduce an air bubble when inserting the septa. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1054080,"guid":"DB4D6F9011B511EB9084D97187CE9039","previous_id":1054081,"previous_guid":"B3E2A56011B511EB9084D97187CE9039","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"2740F1C300E44137ADD107BDD1BA4C0C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Make label"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"65241B05420C4A74AB9F1032452DEF2F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Using acid washed tubing, transfer degassed water from the vacuum flask to serum bottles by creating a siphon. Use a syringe to start the siphon.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Using a siphon avoids pouring the water an potentially reintroducing gas into the water. Take care to keep the tubing ends at the bottom of both the flask and the serum bottle to avoid splashing. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1054081,"guid":"B3E2A56011B511EB9084D97187CE9039","previous_id":1054038,"previous_guid":"9C3A47B011B511EB9084D97187CE9039","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"3F6E2565C5654935A66429AFC9FF5DD4","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Make label"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"FA809B0626944AE991F88403FEA572BA","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Using a vacuum flask, vacuum pump, magnetic stir plate and stir rod, degas 2L of water at \u2265 900 mbar for at least 20 minutes. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1054087,"guid":"187DF7F011BA11EBB6288FB414C2DAB2","previous_id":1054076,"previous_guid":"FC6AFF1011B711EB9084D97187CE9039","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8CB6220BA8944A659E40EC80F5E52855","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Make label"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"29DEBB1E97CE4455924485AC971791D0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">After all the gas is injected, water accumulated in the outflow can be used to re-pressurize the serum bottle. Re-pressuring can increase dissolution (see Klawonn 2015 et al. Front. Microbiology) <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">If there is any air in the outflow syringe, purge this air out prior to re-pressurizing so that only degassed water is being used to re-pressurize the bottle. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1155895,"guid":"E74BB64095DA11EB8A3D8764BD58B9D6","previous_id":1054075,"previous_guid":"448E675011B811EB9084D97187CE9039","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"CC820F29608D4CD4A2441BAAE6917CF4","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Illustration of protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"DBF2B0B12E144816AF65959847B8C208","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Illustration by M. Moynihan<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"F735CF0095DA11EB8A3D8764BD58B9D6","order_id":2,"type_id":23,"title":"file","source":{"source":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/da5ghqee.png","placeholder":"","original_name":"degassing_illustration.png"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">A protocol for making pre-dissolved 15N2 label in sterile seawater<\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1617792229}